ty", "label": "Normalization of inequality: people anchor their evaluation of outcome inequality on what they personally experience, regardless of opportunity distribution", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "public/presentations/experiment/unfairness_inequality.qmd", "source_location": "lines 241-267", "source_url": null, "captured_at": "2025-09-03", "author": "Mauricio Bucca; Mario D. Molina", "contributor": null}, {"id": "public_presentations_experiment_unfairness_inequality_rank_preservation", "label": "Rank preservation: clear majority favor unequal reward distributions that preserve the original winner-loser ranking, across all conditions", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "public/presentations/experiment/unfairness_inequality.qmd", "source_location": "lines 241-250", "source_url": null, "captured_at": "2025-09-03", "author": "Mauricio Bucca; Mario D. Molina", "contributor": null}, {"id": "public_presentations_experiment_unfairness_inequality_fair_inequality", "label": "Fair inequality: perceived 'fair' winner share mirrors participants' own exposure to inequality, holds regardless of opportunity distribution or personal outcome; winners endorse larger gaps as fair", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "public/presentations/experiment/unfairness_inequality.qmd", "source_location": "lines 253-266", "source_url": null, "captured_at": "2025-09-03", "author": "Mauricio Bucca; Mario D. Molina", "contributor": null}, {"id": "public_presentations_experiment_unfairness_inequality_jassos_justice", "label": "Jasso's-like justice (log ratio of observed to fair inequality): losers see actual inequality as slightly greater than fair; winners in high inequality view observed gaps as fair; winners in low inequality feel underpaid and favor larger shares", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "public/presentations/experiment/unfairness_inequality.qmd", "source_location": "lines 269-283", "source_url": null, "captured_at": "2025-09-03", "author": "Mauricio Bucca; Mario D. Molina", "contributor": null}, {"id": "public_presentations_experiment_unfairness_inequality_opportunity_inequality", "label": "Opportunity inequality treatment: equal (random exchange, RA) vs. unequal (regressive exchange, RE) card-exchange rule manipulating equality of opportunity each round", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "public/presentations/experiment/unfairness_inequality.qmd", "source_location": "lines 137-198", "source_url": null, "captured_at": "2025-09-03", "author": "Mauricio Bucca; Mario D. Molina", "contributor": null}, {"id": "public_presentations_experiment_unfairness_inequality_outcome_inequality", "label": "Outcome inequality treatment: low ($2.5 gap) vs. high ($5 gap) payoff difference between winner and loser", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "public/presentations/experiment/unfairness_inequality.qmd", "source_location": "lines 137-198, 376-393", "source_url": null, "captured_at": "2025-09-03", "author": "Mauricio Bucca; Mario D. Molina", "contributor": null}, {"id": "public_presentations_experiment_unfairness_inequality_social_position", "label": "Social position: winner vs. loser of the 5-round card game, determined by rounds won", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "public/presentations/experiment/unfairness_inequality.qmd", "source_location": "lines 137-198", "source_url": null, "captured_at": "2025-09-03", "author": "Mauricio Bucca; Mario D. Molina", "contributor": null}, {"id": "public_presentations_experiment_unfairness_inequality_experimental_platform", "label": "Experimental platform: pre-registered, interactive two-player, 5-round online card game (N=3,335) on CloudResearch Connect, fully crossed 2x2x2 design (opportunity x outcome inequality x social position)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "public/presentations/experiment/unfairness_inequality.qmd", "source_location": "lines 131-197", "source_url": null, "captured_at": "2025-09-03", "author": "Mauricio Bucca; Mario D. Molina", "contributor": n